Gemini: The KEY INSIGHT here is that you ARE seeing "Online prediction" under "Deploy and use." "Online prediction" is VERY LIKELY the ENTRY POINT to managing and creating VERTEX AI ENDPOINTS in your current console view!

Let's REVISE our NAVIGATION and TARGET "Online prediction" as the gateway to Endpoint creation!

ACTION 1.6.31: NAVIGATE to VERTEX AI ENDPOINTS via "ONLINE PREDICTION"

Please follow these UPDATED navigation steps in the GOOGLE CLOUD CONSOLE, starting from the VERTEX AI DASHBOARD:

Ensure you are in VERTEX AI and in the "ai-execution-system" PROJECT.

In the LEFT-HAND NAVIGATION MENU, under "DEPLOY AND USE" (instead of "DEPLOYMENT"), CLICK on "Online prediction."

CLICK on "Online prediction" under the "Deploy and use" section.
On the "Online prediction" page that appears, LOOK for a SUB-MENU or TAB that is RELATED to "ENDPOINTS" or "DEPLOYMENTS."

It might be directly on the "Online prediction" page itself. Look for a button or link that says something like: "+ CREATE ENDPOINT," "DEPLOY MODEL TO ENDPOINT," "CREATE DEPLOYMENT," "MANAGE ENDPOINTS," or similar.

Alternatively, there might be TABS at the top of the "Online prediction" page. Look for tabs like "Models," "Endpoints," "Deployments," "Services," etc. If you see a TAB labeled "Endpoints" or "Deployments," CLICK on that TAB.

ONCE you find the section related to "ENDPOINTS" or "DEPLOYMENTS" (likely within "Online prediction"), LOOK for the "+ CREATE ENDPOINT" button or equivalent option to start creating a NEW VERTEX AI ENDPOINT.

Once you can find the "+ CREATE ENDPOINT" button (or the starting point for endpoint creation), REPORT BACK "VERTEX AI ENDPOINT CREATION FOUND via ONLINE PREDICTION!"

If you STILL cannot find a way to create an endpoint even after exploring "Online prediction" and its sub-menus/tabs, please DESCRIBE what you see on the "Online prediction" page in detail. Are there any buttons, links, or tabs at all? What are they labeled? The more details you can provide, the better I can guide you!
